inn1.comm: back of a length and angling into the right-hander, he hangs back and punches it into the vacant space past midwicket for a couple
bouncer, 134ks, angling into Azhar again. He read it well, safely ducking under it. Ramdin takes it in front of his chest. Nice, TV-friendly carry to the keeper
back of a length and some width outside off, stands up tall and punches it firmly in the gap at the covers
141ks, Joseph hurls it full and outside off, gives it more chance of swinging. This is an outswinger, starts wide. Left alone
this dies on its way to Ramdin. Full and outside off, Azhar reaches out for a drive and is beaten in the channel

slightly overpitched and veering into the pads, Azhar shuffles across, he tends to do that, especially early in the innings. He does not fall over, putting it away wide of midwicket with a flick, the first boundary of the day
square-driven for four! Su-weet. No violence from Sharjeel. Pitched up and angling away from the left-hander from over the wicket, 139ks, eased away through point
Sharjeel opts for force now. Gabriel drags his length back, this is close to off. Not much room to cut, although the length was fine for the shot. Chopped towards backward point now
stump-to-stump line, jabbed onto the pads off an inside edge. The ball trickles to off, and they steal a single

146ks from Gabriel, Azhar does not care. A bit overpitched on middle, steps forward and drives it straight down the ground. He closed the bat-face a touch, but hit is reasonably well past the non-striker
147.1ks, back of a length, played back to the bowler
back of a length and outside off, Azhar is on his tippy toes as he punches confidently to cover. Oh yeah, he has looked confident in this early exchange
Joseph's first ball to Sharjeel is short and outside off, he brings out his favourite short-arm pull and sends it to deep midwicket. It sat up to be hit
good length and angling away outside off from over the wicket, cautiously left alone now
Mid-on dives to his right and makes a good stop. Good length on middle, check-driven down the ground
short and outside off, angling away further past the pull of Sharjeel. He just loves the leg-side region
might have been a cross-seamer, shoots low outside off, pitched short outside off. Beats the scything cut of Sharjeel
strays on the pads, with fine leg inside the circle, easily glanced away past the fielder
shot! Fraction short and outside off, 148ks, flayed away wide of backward point. Went deep in the crease and capitalised on the width
leg-side delivery now, simply diverted off the pads to the left of Ramdin
back of a length and skating in on off stump at 145ks, jabbed to mid-on for a single
back of a length and angling away, 140ks, pushed into the covers
Sharjeel opens the bat-face and steers this length ball to backward point
back of a length on middle, 144ks, Sharjeel swivels on the back foot and pulls stylishly behind square on the leg side. Pakistan run away to 36 in four overs
fired into the pads, no flight, clipped past midwicket
angling into the left-hander, bunted down the ground for one
skidding across the right-hander, dabbed towards point
picked off the pads to the right of short midwicket for one
flat on middle, stays back and short-arms it to midwicket
darted short and just outside off, Sharjeel camps back and slaps it fiercely square through the off side
back of a length and outside off, about 20ks slower than Gabriel, drop-and-run single behind square on off
back of a length on off, guided towards backward point. They take a single via an overthrow, Gabriel who was backing-up let the ball through
Azhar shimmies out. Holder drags his length back. Tickled only to short fine leg
back of a length and angled in, defended back to the bowler
back of a length and angled in on middle, shuffles across and clips through square leg
Sharjeel raises Pakistan's fifty with another slapped four. Fraction short and outside off, cut away through backward point. Third man was inside the circle
sliding across off, forced into the covers
flatter on off, gets forward and pushes back to the bowler
stump-to-stump line, turned to leg
down the track and whipped through midwicket
angled into the left-hander, takes the pad and rolls towards square leg
round-armish ball coming into the left-hander, he punches it down the ground. That's the first over of the day without a boundary
back of a length and cramps him for room, defended to the off side for one
pretty full on off, Azhar presses forward and drives it down to mid-on
full and swerves in from outside off, kept low, and beat him
Azhar steps out and across. Holder is smart enough to drag his length back. Hops, skids, and eventually fends it towards point
length ball on off angled out to backward point
back of a length and outside off, gently run away square through the off side
skiddy ball, keeps low, raps the pad, but the sharp angle was taking it down leg
full on middle, pushed back to the bowler
Sharjeel is happy to stay in the crease. Flat ball on off, whipped from there to long-on
nicked through where first slip may have been. Skidding across the right-hander, he backs away and slashes an outside edge. The ball plugs in the deep near third man
clipped away to deep square leg
length ball angled in, forced down to long-on
back of a length and angling away outside off past the outside edge. Sharjeel was left searching for a dab
length ball on off, this time he succeeds in tapping through point with an open face
Azhar shuffles out and across off again, did not look in complete control. Just deflected it to short fine leg and then took off for a single
glanced off the hips to the leg side
back of a length and outside off, Azhar plays late, opens the face and manipulates it fine on the off side, third man was rather square
back of a length on off, tucked through midwicket
flatter one on middle and leg, worked with the spin towards deep midwicket
drifts back into middle from around the stumps, punched to long on
slider across the batsman, he shapes to cut but is beaten by one that skids on
tucked off his pads towards Benn at deep midwicket, sensible stuff
tossed up over his eyeline, he gets to the pitch of the ball and chips it inside-out to wide long-off. The fielder came haring in, and so it will just be a single
gets outside the line of the stumps and sweeps it powerfully behind short fine leg. Cleverly done. Eliminated the lbw and then played to his strengths
slow turn from outside off, punched wide of cover as they jog through for a single
gets forward to block that quicker one outside off
swept fine, but there's a man coming around to cut that off. Well done, Alzarri Joseph
too full on middle, flicked straight to midwicket
shortens his length, there's some width on offer as well, crunched to deep point
gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks
plays back to a fuller delivery outside off, pushed from the crease to short cover
leans forward and works it with the spin towards long-on. Benn failed to put his left foot out to try and stop that
drifting into middle from around the stumps, Azhar is struck on the pad as he chips out to work it to the leg side, but he was hit outside the line of the stumps
drifting down leg, tickled fine. Gabriel gives it chase and pulls it back in the nick of time
slow turn back into middle, turned to mid-on
gets back into the crease to wrist that past the infield to deep midwicket
prods forward to block a tossed up delivery on middle
looked to flick too early, hit on the pad but the ball pitched outside leg stump
flatter one this time, slow turn gives Sharjeel enough time to hang back and work it past midwicket for an easy single
sees the batsman shaping to sweep and fires it short and wide, Azhar still manages to fetch it from way outside off towards fine leg
cleverly done, stays back and opens the bat face late to bunt it wide of cover for a quick single
beaten by one that fizzes back in. Was looking to cut bit it was too full. The width wasn't there too

drills it straight down the throat of long-on. Benn gives it generous flight, Sharjeel wants to hit that over the ropes, but got a little too close to the ball, which denied him the elevation and power. Relief for West Indies.
drifts into middle, too full as well, defended to the leg side
steps out and works it with the angle to long-on
slides one into the pads, turned to short fine leg
driven with the spin to sweeper cover for an easy single
lovely flight, loop and drift from wide of the crease, Babar does well to not commit into a stroke and waits for the ball to slide in and hit the bat
paddled round the corner, but a touch too risky. The top edge landed to the left of short fine leg.
gets outside the line of the stumps and defends that tossed up delivery
this one is once again a quicker one outside off, defended to cover
touch short, kept low as well, Azhar mistimes a cut to point
once again making room to crunch that through the off side but had to adjust late and block once he realised there was no room
drifting into middle and off from wide of the crease, gets a leading edge that rolls back to the bowler
excellent stop at point by Samuels. It was struck well off the back foot, Samuels threw himself to his left. It was going away from him, but he did well
turns the incoming delivery to square leg
makes a bit of room and drives it with the spin to long-off for an easy single
steps out and eases it back to the bowler, who dives to his left on the followthrough to stop that
slows it down nicely, there's some turn as well, stays inside the crease and eases it wide of cover
driven through the line to long-off for an easy single
punched with the spin to wide long-on
this is the other one, the carrom ball that breaks away to deceive him, beaten
saved by an inside edge. This one skids straight on as he looks to work it across the line
stretches out and opens the bat face late to ease it down to deep point
tossed up outside off, he got to the pitch, underneath the ball and crashed it into the gap at deep extra cover
once again there's width for him to drive through the line, down to the boundary rider at cover
is made to lunge forward to block that incoming delivery
steps out and brings his wrists into play to ease that down to long on
generous flight on that, driven back to the bowler
a lazy effort at midwicket ensures a single. Narine tried to stick out his boot instead of bending down to stop that flick
opens the bat face to steer it to the off side, finds cover
sees the batsman giving him the charge and fires it into middle, turned to midwicket
powerful sweep from outside off, but straight to Pollard at deep midwicket

steps out and lofts him cleanly over the infield. The timing is delightful too as the ball clears the ropes quite easily. Effortlessly done. He wasn't afraid to step out, and once he did,  there was authority and intent
gets forward and blocks the quicker one
this one's the carrom ball, but it was too full for it to turn away, driven straight to cover
driven into the gap, past Holder at extra cover
gets outside the line of the stumps and turns it with the spin towards midwicket. Relief writ large on Azhar's face as he acknowledges the applause of his team-mates. Half-century
skips out, probably got too close to the pitch, digging back to Benn
leaves the crease again, this is solidly dabbed behind square on the leg side
slightly short and outside off, ventures deep in the crease and forces to the covers
much slower through the air, down the track, meets the pitch, and secures a single down to long-off
slid in on middle, shuffles down and across as he  bunts it square through the leg side. Busy footwork
stays still and punches this well-flighted delivery to cover
back of a length on off from over the wicket, jabbed to mid-on
back of a length and outside off, has room, and forces through backward point
length ball on a fourth-stump line, pushed into the covers with hard hands
length and outside off, slashed away in the gap at backward point now
fraction short on off, 138ks, rushes Azhar onto a pull. He sends  a top-edge fluttering over short midwicket. Mid-on, running to his right, had no chance as well
back of a length, 140ks, outside off, punched out through the covers again
uses his feet and calmly drives to long-off after meeting the pitch of the ball
pushed through fullish on the off stump, no turn, Azhar goes low and crunches a slog-sweep over midwicket, one-bounce four
shuffles out and flicks behind square for one
slides on outside off, steps back and punches through cover
more use of the feet, check-driven to cover, tossed-up delivery from Benn
shorter and wider, allows him to go back and cut to sweeper cover
short on off, cramps him for room, mis-hits a pull to long-on
back of a length and outside off, laced to deep backward point. Gabriel's front foot has strayed
back of a length on middle, 146.3ks, Azhar, having opened himself up at the crease, slogs it over square leg. Narine takes the catch in the deep, but it amounts to nothing
back of a length on off, played back to the bowler
length and outside off, forward and slotted into the covers with a drive
shortish on off, hops and deflects the ball down to fine leg
back of a length on a fourth-stump line, 143ks. Azam absorbs the pace and pushes to cover
length ball angled in on off from round the wicket, defended
skips out, gets a short ball outside off, hit to long-on
sees some flight, dances out, meets the pitch. Picks it up and flicks it over midwicket. Pristine
straight delivery on middle, driven down to long-on
flatter and outside off, Azhar goes low again. Unleashes a slog-sweep and sends it over midwicket for six. He's got those big shots!
leaves the crease, gets close to the pitch, smothers any spin, and secures a single down to long-off
wide of the crease and angled into a jab to mid-on

nicked past Ramdin for four! Gabriel sinks to his knees. Angled in and straightens a bit outside off, 146ks. Azam drives away from the body, the hands doing all the work. Edged through where first slip may have been. Rolls away to the third-man fence. First false shot from Azam, that control percentage will dip now
length and outside off, guided behind square on the off side for one
short on off, hops up and works it through square leg
length and outside off, hit out to the right of sweeper cover with slicing finish
length and outside off, presses forward and drives to mid-off
short and wide outside off, skips back and cuts firmly through cover-point
back of a length and outside off, smeared to long-off
flighted length ball outside off, Azhar slog-sweeps, loses his shape, and misses
fetches this offbreak from outside off, and slogs it across the line to deep square leg
floated up on off, clipped to midwicket
Azhar goes low pre-meditates a sweep. Takes it from outside off and hits towards deep square leg
starts the new spell with a leg-side wide, which beat the attempted glance
goes wide of the crease and angles a short ball on top of off, Azhar gets on top of the bounce. He leaps and punches it ,bisecting mid-on and mid-off. Charming stroke
too straight in line, helped down to fine leg
short and wide outside off, real gift from Joseph. The offcutter went wrong. He tears the wrapper and smears it through cover
slower-ball bouncer, another offcutting ball, check-pulled behind square on the leg side
full and straight, flicked to midwicket
back of a length and wide outside off, reaches out and steers down to third man
pushed through outside off, forced to sweeper cover
non-turning ball outside off, short stride, opens the face, and guides to point
quick skiddy ball on off, kept out
nice offbreak, spins back in, back of a length, punched down to long-on
swept from outside off to deep midwicket
shorter offbreak, hangs back and punches down to long-on
glanced off the hips through backward square leg, third fifty-plus score in a row for Azam. He's looking good for three figures
short on the stumps, pulled behind square on the leg side
back of a length and angled in, turned to midwicket
short and outside off, gets on top of the bounce and cracks a cut to sweeper cover
short on middle, rolls his wrists, and pulls to fine leg
short  on middle, hops, and fends to midwicket
back of length delivery on middle and leg, tucked to deep square leg
pulled in front of square, and he's split the gap to perfection. Deep square leg and long-on converged, but the timing was just too good.
stays inside the crease and dabs the length ball to the off side
punched down the ground, but straight to mid-on this time
cramped for room as he plays the short-arm jab down to long-on. He wanted to hit it over midwicket
chopped to point, looks for the single but Azhar sends him back
pulled, and pulled well. Alzarri digs one in short in the mid-130s, slapped in front of square to the boundary rider
flayed on the up to deep cover

imperious! This is a buffet ball that was dug in short. It was sitting up nicely for Azhar to swivel onto the back foot and pull him into the deep midwicket boundary. He didn't need to keep the ball down as there was no one there. What struck you immediately about the stroke was the time and control he had
cut hard, a misfield at point allows a single. That it was only a misfield was because of Pollard's big hands. Any other fielder and that would have raced away to the boundary
punched on the up but straight to Holder at cover
mistimes the pull this time to midwicket, got the toe end of the bat and was perhaps a touch too early into the stroke as well
full delivery sliding into the pads, defended to midwicket
incoming length ball on middle, dabbed down to third man
length ball outside off, forced off the front foot to mid-off, couldn't free his arms on that occasion
hops across the stumps and helps it down to fine leg. He looked to hit it hard, but changed his mind perhaps fearing a top edge as there was a man in the deep for just that

this is a super strike. Half-volley at a friendly pace outside off, Azam makes a bit of room, gets underneath the delivery and lofts him inside-out. One bounce into the wide long-off bounce. Free flow of the bat in a delightful arc. This is beautiful batting, I must say
dabbed down to third man, clever stuff, will keep strike
driven inside-out to long-off for an easy single
drops it gently towards the off side, looks for the single but is sent back
steps out and punches it down the ground to long-on
short, wide outside off, he goes back deep into the crease to pull that one towards deep midwicket
eased with the spin past a diving Holder at cover, good work by Gabriel at long-off. Ran around quickly to hurl the throw
loopy delivery that drifts into middle, played back to the bowler
works the length ball outside off into the gap between midwicket and long-on
short-arm jab to deep midwicket. This one was dug in short again, but kept a touch low

appeal for lbw, but the umpire says not out. Close, close call. He was a long way across the stumps as he tried to work it fine. Surely the only thing that could have saved him was an inside-edge, but a leg-bye has been signalled.  West Indies didn't review.  Trust me, it was really close but Hawk-eye says the ball would have missed the top of leg stump marginally. Looked a lot closer than that
short, wide outside off, slapped into the gap at deep point, back for the second before Pollard could rush in the throw
stays inside the crease and dabs the length ball to the off side
punched to mid-off, but they don't take the single
good, clean chip down the ground. Right in between long-on and long-off. He didn't to hit it too hard
punched off the back foot to long off, jogs the single
didn't get to the pitch of the ball but still went through to drive that inside-out to long-off
forced back to the bowler this time
once again, not to the pitch but still pushes it firmly to cover
punched past the infield to the man at sweeper cover
width on offer and he's split the gap between point and short third man. Point precision batting this. Opened the bat face late to find the gap
floated a touch fuller outside off, driven on the up to deep cover
sliding into the pads, worked to wide long-on for an easy single
worked off his hip, good work by Samuels who came rushing in from deep square leg to stop that
slower delivery this time, but once again it was a touch fuller, worked to deep midwicket
'help yourself' delivery on the pads, tucked towards deep fine leg
flatter one on middle from around the stumps, punched to long-on
works it straight to midwicket this time

cuts, and cuts well to pick the gap at deep point.  Becomes the first Pakistan ODI captain to score three centuries.  What a way to silence his critics. Was under fire coming into the game, and this can't be a bad way to come back into form. Has come at a strike rate of close to 100. Pumped his fists after getting to the landmark
squeezed back to the bowler, didn't get underneath that one
too full outside off, squeezed to deep cover for an easy single
cuts, but finds short third man
pulled past Pollard at deep midwicket

has perished in his quest to up the scoring rate. Looks to go over mid-off but was completely deceived by the slower one that cut back in to beat his swing and hit the stumps. He was looking away towards midwicket when the wild bat swing missed the line of the ball, clearly no position to be in, but that can be discussed later. He walks off to a round of applause from the sparse crowd and his team-mates. This has been a determined knock at a time when he really needed it
whipped straight to Pollard at midwicket
hops back and punches it to cover, a misfield by Narine gives them the second. Poor, really
taps it gently towards point, Azam was already halfway down the pitch in anticipation of a run. Completed quite easily
sliding into middle and leg, punched to Lewis at mid-on, quick single taken
starts off with a gentle delivery outside off, slapped to sweeper cover
punched back to the bowler
slow turn back into middle and leg, worked wide of deep midwicket, excellent running. Malik pushed his partner, who completed the second quite easily
slider outside off, this one turned away a wee bit, Malik is foxed by the turn as he bottom-edges a cut that Ramdin gathers rather well. Double-strike for West Indies. It kept a touch low as well
opens the bat face to steer it straight to short third man
worked with the spin to deep midwicket
back of a length and outside off, leans back and glides it to backward point
slanting down leg, past the glance, wide
good length on a fourth-stump line, cushioned with soft hands to point
dug in outside off, drags a pull to deep midwicket
leg-stump ball, ticked away to fine leg
slower cutter, clipped down to long-on
slower and loopier outside off, knocked down to long-off. Sarfraz wants the second, and hares back for it. He is perhaps the quickest runner in the Pakistan team
tossed outside off, swept to fine leg
flatter and quicker outside off, cracked to sweeper cover
flighted and outside off, dabbed into the cover-point region
slides on without any turn outside off, lashed to cover
slightly short and wide outside off, chopped out to sweeper cover
length and outside off, square-driven for two. Excellent running
pitched up on off, driven down to long-on
goes wide of the crease and angles it down leg, wide
back of a length and angled in, stabs and manages an inside edge that dribbles past the leg stump
slower offcutter, worked behind square for a comfortable two
stands tall, takes this short ball from outside off and punches to long-off. Moves to 99. Coach Arthur is on his feet
loopy offcutter, takes it on the full, 116ks, whipped to mid-on. Sarfraz did not meet the pitch of the ball
tucked to midwicket

There it is! Babar Azam becomes only the third Pakistan batsman to score hundreds in three successive ODI innings. He is embraced bt Sarfraz. He then celebrates the landmark with a sajdah. Pushed through wide outside off,  drilled through the covers
clipped away through backward square leg
down the track and hacked to long-on
slides on outside off, drilled through the covers
back of a length and outside of, carved to cover
off-stump full toss from the returning Joseph, pumped to long-on
cutter outside off, backs away outside leg and creams it on the up over cover
back of a length on middle, slogged to long-on
wide yorker, angled out to short third man
low full toss on middle, whipped away to deep midwicket, KP hunts the ball down
very full on off, clears his front leg and hits it to long-on
wide of the crease and angled on middle, driven straight down the ground for a double

That's the first boundary since the 37th over! Down the track, gets a short-ball offcutter, pulled over square leg. Lewis runs to his left, lazy effort, gives away a four. Pollard is quite peeved at that limp effort. He was a bit lazy to bend down and cut it off. Attempted only with one hand
slower offcutter, smacked over midwicket
wide of the crease and cuts into Sarfraz, stabbed back at KP
another slower cutter, skips out and manufactures his own pace. Thumped over midwicket

bowled'em! Pollard pulls the finger-on-the-lip celebration, his 50 ODI wicket in his 101st game. Azam shuffled across off for a little scoop. He does not put bat on ball. Pollard hits the leg stump with a pretty full delivery. Azam receives a great reception from his team-mates. Azhar gives him a big hug
full on off, clears his front leg and belts the ball towards long-on
yorker on the leg stump, tickled past short fine leg
good length on middle and leg, keeps a bit low, deflected towards square leg

Rizwan has been given out lbw, after a lengthy deliberation. He wants a review. Height may be an issue? Back of a length indipper, cuts in sharply, and strikes the flap of the back pad in front of middle and off or thereabouts. No signs of an inside edge. The tracker shows that the ball would graze the top of middle. Ump Palliyaguruge's on-field call is upheld
full on middle and leg, whipped stylishly to wide long-on
short on off, controls a pull to deep midwicket
shuffles away outside leg and is followed by KP. Driven straight down the ground
Sarfraz moves away outside leg again, this is a short offcutter, pulled from outside leg to deep midwicket

KP bowls it from behind the crease. Slower offcutter, Imad is way early into a slog-sweep. He's hit outside the line of off, I suppose. Not given. Holder calls for a review, more out of hope rather than conviction. Even if it had pitched in line, the cutter would have missed off. Tracker shows it would have missed another set of stumps
races down the track, takes a short ball from the stumps and belts to mid-off
low full toss outside off, swats it to long-off
KP bowls it from wide of the crease, Sarfraz slinks away outside leg. This is banged in on leg stump, forced out to the covers
full on the stumps, Sarfraz shuffles across off, loses his balance and topples over. But manages to scoop it in the air, fine of short fine leg. The yorker didn't go well for Joseph
Sarfraz shuffles outside leg, this is banged in short and outside leg, top-edged wide of short fine leg. 300 up for Pakistan
Sarfraz pre-meditates again, goes away outside leg, this is a wide cutter outside off. Reaches out and flays it away to backward point
Imad shuffles across off now, ramps it over the keeper's head, even though he din't middle the away-cutter from Joseph
back of a length and bounces over the top of the stumps, as Imad shuffles outside leg now. Misses a reverse-scoop over short third man
holes out to deep midwicket! Banged in short and rises just outside off, Imad Wasim aims to swat-pull it away. Ends up flat-batting it away, tennis-style, to Darren Bravo
offcutter from wide of the crease, beats the slash outside off
slower and outside off, knocked down to long-off
Sarfraz backs away outside leg, slower offcutter from KP. Sarfraz aims a leg-side slog and skies it over the bowler's head
back of a length offcutter outside off, shovelled down to long-on
steps out, KP bowls a quick yorker outside off. Beaten
slower cutter outside off, hacked to square leg off an inside edge. Hoodwinked by the change of pace or maybe not. Pollard has been bowling a bevy of cutters

inn2.comm: angled in on middle from round the wicket, he starts off by attacking the stumps, worked to midwicket from the crease
inducker from Imad, swerves in and raps the pad as Kraigg moves back and pokes. It was slipping down leg, though
drifting into the pads, glanced towards short fine leg
skids on off, defended into cover on the back foot
much fuller and outside off, Lewis presses forward and drives to extra-cover
zips through outside off, hint of extra bounce that surprises Lewis. He pats it down like a gambolling puppy
angling into leg stump, glided fine on the leg side for four. Warm-up ball, put away. Fine leg is rather wide
length ball angled into off, Kraigg shuffles across and defends to midwicket
away-swinger, starts wide outside off and moves way further, wide called. Left alone by Kraigg

angled in towards off stump and leaves Kraigg outside off. He is completely opened up as the ball swings past the outside edge. Kraigg could have pressed forward to meet that ball. His poor technique made it look like a magic ball
full and largely holds its line outside off, ignored
Sohail grunts as he sends a full ball outside off, 136ks, left alone again
awayswinger again, starts wide, another easy leave for Kraigg
skids through on off, no turn, pushed to cover on the front foot
sliding across the off stump, slashes and misses outside off on the back foot
flatter and fired outside off, stays back and punches to mid-off
pushed through at the leg stump, blocked back to Imad
speared into the leg stump, goes low and sweeps it fine of short fine leg. Not middled, but good enough for three, Lewis' first runs in ODI cricket
another inducker, on the stumps, nudged into the midwicket region on the back foot
good length ball angled in, Kraigg goes forward and across to negotiate it
full and outside off, Kraigg drives away from the body, his foot was nowhere close to the pitch. Ends up dragging an inside edge past the leg stump. It's cut off in the deep
short and Kraigg has the width to free his arms. Cracked away through square point for four
lands it full and wide outside off, swings away further, left alone. Late movement, tests Sarfraz as well. He flings to his right and collects it. Excellent save from the keeper. Off-side wide
full on a fourth-stump line, probably a little too full, Kraigg presses forward and pushes-drives it straight of mid-on
awayswinger outside off, left alone
another awayswinger, no shot offered
fired across off, chopped to backward point
slider on the stumps, hangs back and pushes to cover
jabbed from a fourth-stump line through midwicket for a couple
shoots low on off, dabbed to square leg
rolls on middle in a straight line, defended back to Imad
skiddy on off, pushed back to Imad
another wide awayswinger, off-side wide
back of a length and angled in, Kraigg comes halfway forward and blocks to mid-on
very full on off, dug out to mid-on for a well-judged single
overpitched outside off, steps forward and drives to extra-cover
short and angled away, stabbed to cover
straying into the hips, handsomely flicked away through wide mid-on
full on middle, shuffles across off and pushes the ball to mid-on
flighted and outside off, driven down to long-on
slid across off, keeps a bit low, chopped away towards cover point
another shooter outside off, stoops low, and keeps it out
slightly short and outside off, angling away, rocks back and forces it to extra-cover
short on the leg stump, skips back and banishes it behind square with a strong pull
short and angled across off, Lewis is quick to rock back again. This is cut away fiercely square through the off side. When Imad gives you width, you've got to capitalise
back of a length, angled in straightens around off. Takes the outside edge to third man
length and outside off, punched to extra-cover

Sohail strikes on return! Given out. Lewis and Kraigg have a chat. WI opt for a review. Good length on middle,  he plays around the front pad. Struck on the knee-roll of the front pad as Lewis is pinned on the crease. Did it pitch in line, though? HawkEye shows that it  pitched marginally outside leg. First decision that has been overturned out of seven in this series

shuffles across off, plays around the front pad again. Not given, and Pakistan review now. This is tighter. Full, hit well below the knee-roll, hits him in front of middle. This straight ball would have definitely hit the stumps. Sohail denied again. It pitched marginally outside leg again, says the tracker. Phew!
full on off, presses forward to defend it back to Sohail
length and outside off, patted to the covers
thuds into the pad, misses the flick, may have pitched outside leg. It came in, and Pakistan have lost their review
length and on a fourth-stump line, defended
back of a length and outside off, punched with a straight bat to the man at mid-off
back of a length and angling in, turned to leg
back of a length on off, forced to mid-on
back of a length and outside off, rises on top of the bounce, punching to extra-cover
full and outside off, hits on the up, thrashing a drive over extra-cover

the leg stump is titled back! Lewis' front leg shuffles across early, he can't escape now. This good length ball swings in, having started from outside leg, from over the wicket, and takes the leg stump. You don't need the umpires and the tracker for this. Many would have looked to play it straight or towards mid-on. Lewis was aiming for midwicket
half-volley on middle, drilled straight down the ground, so much so it rattles the stumps at the non-striker's end
awayswinger outside off, dies on its way to Sarfraz. They sneak in a bye
length and outside off, jabbed to the off side
back of a length and angled in, worked to square leg
acrobatic stop by Umar Akmal at point, saved a couple of runs at least.
rapped on the pad as he looks to work it off the pads. Fortunately for him, the ball pitched miles outside leg stump
width on offer this time, glided away to third man for an easy single
nips back into middle, Bravo presses forward and defends firmly to cover
stays right back inside the crease and opens the bat face late to steer it to point
jags back in to take the inside edge as Bravo pushes forward with a straight bat, midwicket fielder was late to react  as they pinch a run that shouldn't have been conceded
beaten on an expansive drive, it was floated full outside off, looks like it slipped off his hands too. Lucky to get away
loopy delivery that drifts in to middle, squeezed back down the pitch
tossed up on off stump, driven firmly to cover
beaten by one that slides on. Bravo played for the turn as this went past the inside edge.
driven on the up to sweeper cover
slider across the batsman from around the stumps, worked to midwicket
length ball on middle, defended back down the pitch
squared up one that leaves him late but luckily Bravo loosened his grip while playing at that, which meant the ball didn't carry to the keeper
crunching off drive but straight to mid-off
once again he's squared up in defense. The ball deviated away a wee bit to open him up
firm push on the up, but can't pierce the packed off side ring. Straight to cover
slower delivery at length on middle and leg, defended to the off side
would have been bowled around his legs had it not hit his right boot. Too early into the sweep
worked with the spin towards deep midwicket
drifts back into middle, he stretches forward and taps it to cover
misses a flick down leg side, keeper does well to move to his right to gather that
deceived in flight as he presses forward, offers a dead bat to that delivery to block
beaten fair and square by one that spins away to whizz past the edge
makes a bit of room to punch that into the deep cover region
cut away but another good stop by Umar Akmal at point
punched down to long on with the spin
sees the width and slashes that into the gap at point. Welcome boundary for West Indies. Poor delivery to release all the pressure that was building up. Bread and butter stroke as they call it
slider into middle and leg, tickled away past short fine leg. The fielder there dived over the ball, Malik drags it back
slow turn back in, defended back to the bowler
bunted back down the pitch, looked like a certain single until the bowler threw himself full-length to his left to stop that
defended back to the bowler
taps it into the on side for a quick single, the midwicket fielder was a bit too deep
that's a good stroke. Touch short, flayed past the cover fielder
slips this one on leg stump, worked wide of square leg
drilled down the ground with the spin to long-off
shapes to cut but this one spins back in to cramp him for room, still manages to dab it down to short third man
quicker one on middle from around the stumps, played back to the bowler
gives it air this time, the ball fizzes upon landing just around off, he gets forward and smothers the spin
punched down the ground to long-off
looks to slog across the line but changes his stroke, the cut is hit straight to point
walks across the stumps but the bowler tosses it up well outside off to leave Bravo with no choice but to turn it to short midwicket
rank long hop and this time Bravo connects. Uses the depth of the crease to generate the power as he pulls him over the ropes at deep midwicket. Much-needed that and they need more of it
nicely flighted on middle, turned to midwicket
nurdled off the pads towards deep square leg
beaten in flight, gets a thick edge down to short third man

this one spun back in to beat Brathwaite's attempted tuck with the spin across the line. He was struck in front of middle. Although he was fairly a long way forward, he was struck below the knee roll. There was no inside edge either, so third umpire S Ravi had a straightforward deicsion to make
this one is bowled a lot slower through the air as he lands it on off stump, not much turn, blocked
defended to midwicket
beaten by a yorker-length delivery outside off that squeezes through before he could jam his bat down
driven on the up to deep cover
beaten by a full-length delivery. He made the mistake of poking at it from the crease. Luckily it was outside off. Completely opened up as he stabbed at that
struck on the pad but the ball was angling down
angles it into the pads, flicked to midwicket again
off the mark with a tight single to mid-off, a direct hit at the bowler's end would have made it interesting
floats it up on middle and leg, plays it straight to square leg
forced down to long-off as he jogs a single
gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it with the spin to sweeper cover
super stop by Nawaz at deep midwicket, threw himself to his left after covering good ground to stop that lofted hit, saved a couple of runs
makes room and cuts it to point where Wahab stops courtesy a diving effort
Azhar can't cut that off at the edge of the ring at midwicket, punched down to long-on
big appeal for lbw as Bravo is beaten in an attempt to work it across the line. Clearly beaten for pace by that full-length delivery. The ball would have missed leg stump
driven on the up to deep cover, Bravo called for two but it was a very optimistic call really

bat face turns in his hand as he looks to work it wide of square leg, the ball runs down to fine leg from where an accurate throw hits the stumps direct at the striker's end. Samuels was ambling down the pitch but just managed to get in
width on offer, he's smashed the cover off that, a diving stop at point by Rizwan keeps that down to a single
right behind the line of that full-length delivery as he solidly defends

the struggle is finally over for Darren Bravo, and it's the extra pace that's done him in here. Bravo, perhaps expecting a short ball, was camping back. This one was floated at length around off. The ball fizzed through after pitching and a tentative poke away from the body found the edge as Sarfaz accepted it gleefully.
defended straight to midwicket
width on offer, slapped straight to cover where Azhar pulls off a super stop diving to his left
drives, gets the edge. Straight to short third man. Pressure building again
lofted over the infield to Azam at long-on
turned with the spin towards deep square, off the mark straightaway. He wanted the second but the throw was a flat one at the bowler's end

this one has been hammered into the deep cover boundary. Picked the vacant space to perfection. Fractionally short from Malik, there was no turn so Samuels had the width to slap that away. Found the middle of the bat too
floats one back in from around the stumps, defended to mid-off

Oh, dear. What a terrible, terrible way to be dismissed. Ramdin chopped this to point and took a couple of paces down the pitch before turning his back on his partner. By then, Samuels had run almost the entire length of the pitch. Rizwan, who picked the ball up had the awareness to run towards the stumps and take the bails off rather than fire a throw. West Indies are crashing and burning here in the desert
driven well but straight to cover
reverse swing? This one came back in a long way to roll off the inside edge to the leg side. Beaten for pace again but he somewhat managed to defend
nearly chopped that back onto the stumps. The ball shaves past the stumps, they steal a run
off the mark with a push wide of midwicket. This time there's certainty in the running
beaten by grip and turn as he prods forward to one that leaves him
too short, enough time to get back and punch it wide of midwicket
not all that short to cut, chops that to point
slider that fizzes back in, almost Jadeja-like, Ramdin is late on a defensive stroke, gets it on the top part of the bat
loopy delivery, squeezed to point
punched down to long on
defends from the crease. Once again the ball came back in a long way to cramp him for room
near chopped that onto the stumps. Pushes outside the line of that length ball, the thick edge flies past leg stump. There was no fine leg fielder on this occasion
crunching cover drive to the boundary rider
gets on top of the bounce and fends that incoming short delivery
hit high on the thigh pad. Pollard is caught hopping and jumping as he looks to turn that off his hip. 146 clicks from Wahab
hustled for pace and bounce, somehow manages to turn it to the on side as they squeeze through for a single
drifts in on off, patted towards backward point with an angled bat
too full on middle, punchily driven down to long-on
looped up outside off, spins away past the skittish waft of KP
good length on a fourth-stump line, defended
too straight in line, whipped towards wide long-on
pitched up on middle, driven back at the bowler
full on middle, driven down to long-on
flat and turning away, goes back and flays it down to wide long-off
slightly short and outside off, cut out to sweeper cover
tossed up and drifts in, takes the inside edge and rolls to leg
skiddy one, shoots low outside off, shovelled down to long-on
straight ball on middle, clipped through midwicket
full and just a shade outside off, jabbing drive to extra-cover
lobbed up outside off, front-foot drive to long-off
drifts in the air, middle-stump line, played back to Nawaz
slides on outside off, pushed into the covers for a quick single
very full on off, bottom-hand dominates the drive to extra-cover
fired outside off, hint of width, rocks back and chops straight to backward point
full and outside off, Pollard bunts a single to long-off
arrowed in with the arm on middle, played back to Imad
much slower through the air on middle, blocked towards midwicket
tossed up on middle, knocked to long-on for one
Imad gives this some air on off, KP is forward to smother it
flatter on middle and leg, turned around the corner
Malik runs in from long-off, and snaps up a tumbling catch. Nicely judged. Well-flighted ball, drifts into KP. Nawaz has him stretching forward and skying a loft. KP's underwhelming UAE tour is over
tossed full on middle, driven to long-off
rolls on middle, played back to the bowler
length ball drifts in, takes the inside edge and runs to leg
back of a length and outside off, punched to cover
slightly short and outside off, stays back and punches to the left of the bowler
leg-stump ball, eased behind square on the leg side
length ball on off, firmly pushed to long-off
drifts in and turns away, pokes an outside edge towards point
lobbed up outside off, forward and tapped to extra-cover
quicker on off, hit to long-on
tossed up and drifts in on middle, quietly blocked back to the bowler
full on middle and leg, whipped out to wide long-on
drifts into the right-hander, dips, pushed to extra-cover
hint of turn away, length ball, pushed to extra-cover again
round-armish ball, on the pads, flicked behind square on the leg side
Holder backs away outside leg, shows some intent. Delightfully driving it inside-out over extra-cover. He used his reach to good effect and manufactured a six
faster on middle and leg, clipped to long-on
back of a length on off, pushed to mid-on
back of a length on off, glided through backward point
off-stump yorker, tails in, reverse swing? dug out to extra-cover
good length on a fourth-stump line, presses forward and dabs to extra-cover
length and outside off, patted to the right of extra-cover
very full and swings in from wide of the crease, jabs an inside edge through midwicket
length ball swerves in, takes the inside edge and rolls to long leg
shortish on off, drop-and-run single to extra-cover
Holder makes room outside leg,  short and wide outside off. Slashed hard in the air. Rizwan dives to his right from backward point and could only finger-tip it away. Tough chance put down
back of a length inducker, squirted to extra-cover
good length and straightens a bit outside off, wafts and misses
back of a length and angled in, turned to short midwicket
good length and swings away outside off, draws him forward and beats the outside edge
full and around off, driven to mid-off on the front foot
full and outside off, shimmies out and laces a drive through extra-cover
slower ball, perhaps an offcutter into the pads, tickled to short fine leg
back of a length and tails in, hit down the ground to long-on
back of a length on off, punched out towards mid-off
short and just outside off, cramps Ramdin for room. Stabbed back to Hasan
good length and swerves in, clipped to midwicket
another one that seams back in, dabbed through square leg
Holder steps away outside leg, this low full toss is whipped through square leg
yorker, 140ks, tails in, jammed out off an inside edge
back of a length and skating into the right-hander, punched to midwicket
angled into the right-hander, tailing in further, shortish, dabbed with soft hands towards cover
short and width outside off, Holder capitalises, crunching it through backward point
good length and angled in, dabs a single through point
back of a length and outside off, opens the bat-face and guides it to backward point
back of a length and outside off, chopped to backward point
sharply angled in towards off stump, blocked back to Wahab
good length and snakes in, Holder drives and gets an inside edge onto the pad. The ball wanders away towards cover
back of a length and outside off, punched to backward point
short angled in, cramps him for room, skewed off the inside half to midwicket
full toss on off, pushed only as far as mid-off
short and angled in, cramped for room again, played back down the pitch
yorker, curls in on middle and leg, squeezed through square leg
back of a length and angled in, pokey drive back to the bowler
short and outside off, Holder leaps and rides it to backward point. Overthrow from Pakistan concedes a single
back of a length and outside off, jabbed to extra-cover
short, angled in, nips in off the surface, Ramdin loses his shape as he aims a lusty club and misses
short and wide outside off, cut to backward point
good length veers in from wide of the crease, he may have jammed an inside edge onto the pad. Ramdin weathers the lbw appeal
length ball on off, tapped towards extra-cover

Imad returns and provides the breakthrough. Holder steps away outside leg, aims for a massive mow over midwicket possibly. He makes no connection. Imad does, hitting off with a straight delivery. WI six down
pushed through, sliding across off, past the outside edge
bunted off the pads to the leg side
slower through the air, turns in, worked to square leg
slid in on leg stump, poked back to Imad
slides a wayward short delivery down leg, neat take by Sarfraz

steps out to flick but is beaten by one that skids straight on. Sarfraz effects the simplest of stumpings. Didn't make any effort to get to the pitch of the ball, neither did he try to get back into the crease once he was beaten. Too easy for Pakistan at the moment.
gets forward and defends the tossed up delivery back down the pitch
prods forward and blocks
sharp turn back into middle, defended back down the pitch

as easy as eating chips for the fielder at short third man. Benn looks to play the reverse sweep, but the ball bounced a bit more to take the top edge as Sohail Khan, who it appeared was blinded by the lights, took it comfortably in the end.
nips back in from outside off, defended gently
keeps coming back in to cramp him for room, gets a thick inside edge back to the bowler
every now and then he'll drift down in the quest for pace. This time, Ramdin was up to the task as he tickled that into the fine leg boundary
drops it into the off side gently for a quick single
squared up in defense. The ball was floated in full but jagged away late to open him up. No damage done in the end
rip roaring bouncer but Alzarri Joseph is up for the challenge as he neatly ducks under that
short and wide outside off, smeared to deep point
pushed through quicker on middle and leg, he pushes outside the line to get an inside edge to the leg side
tucked behind square on the leg side for an easy single
chopped to point, it was an arm-ball that cramped him for room this time
lofted inside-out to wide long-off, got to the pitch of the ball on that occasion
neat little flick into the deep backward square leg region

100 ODI wickets for Wahab!  That would have got most tailenders. Bangs one in short from around the stumps, too quick for Joseph as he looks to pull, the bat face turns skywards as the top edge is taken easily by Shoaib Malik, who didn't have to move an inch at short midwicket. The end is near
another short ball angling in, Gabriel ways out of the way comfortably this time
bowls fuller this time to bluff the batsman, Gabriel somehow manages to bring his bat down to the ball and defend
floated full outside off, driven wide of mid-off
wayward delivery on the seventh stump down leg side, keeper dives full length to his left to stop that with one glove
hit on the box as the ball cuts back in to beat his forward push. Ouch!

that's the end of that. Gets a thick inside edge to square leg. No sooner than it hit the bat, Ramdin was off for the single without looking at his partner. Hassan Ali, who initially wanted to run to the stumps, lobbed the throw to Rizwan, who was backing up from point. He then ran to the stumps to whip the bails off with Ramdin nowhere in sight after being sent back
